From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0055/N] add os/bsd/decoder_bsd_elf.cpp for non-Apple BSD ElfDecoder::demangle

`ElfDecoder::demangle` is declared in
`src/hotspot/share/utilities/decoder_elf.hpp` and called from
`decoder_elf.cpp`, but the *implementation* lives in
`src/hotspot/os/linux/decoder_linux.cpp` (Linux-only). On non-Apple BSD
the link fails with:

  undefined reference to _ZN10ElfDecoder8demangleEPKcPci

`os/bsd/decoder_machO.cpp` only handles `__APPLE__`. Add a sibling
`os/bsd/decoder_bsd_elf.cpp` that defines `ElfDecoder::demangle` for
non-Apple BSD using the same `abi::__cxa_demangle` recipe as the
Linux implementation.

The HotSpot build auto-includes all `.cpp` files in `os/bsd/`, so no
makefile change is needed; the `#ifndef __APPLE__` guard ensures the
file compiles to empty under macOS.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md (patch 0055)

--- /dev/null
+++ b/src/hotspot/os/bsd/decoder_bsd_elf.cpp
@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@
+/*
+ * Copyright (c) 1997, 2018, Oracle and/or its affiliates. All rights reserved.
+ * DO NOT ALTER OR REMOVE COPYRIGHT NOTICES OR THIS FILE HEADER.
+ *
+ * This file is part of stopless-java-gc Phase 1; adapts the Linux ElfDecoder
+ * demangle implementation for FreeBSD/CheriBSD. Same C++ ABI + libc++.
+ */
+
+#ifndef __APPLE__
+
+#include "jvm.h"
+#include "utilities/decoder_elf.hpp"
+
+#include <cxxabi.h>
+
+bool ElfDecoder::demangle(const char* symbol, char *buf, int buflen) {
+  int   status;
+  char* result;
+  if ((result = abi::__cxa_demangle(symbol, NULL, NULL, &status)) != NULL) {
+    jio_snprintf(buf, buflen, "%s", result);
+    ::free(result);
+    return true;
+  }
+  return false;
+}
+
+#endif // !__APPLE__
